Titolo: Nautilus (video game)

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Nautilus is a 1982 video game for the Atari 8-bit family of home computers. It was created by Mike Potter and distributed by Synapse Software. In contrast to later releases from Synapse, it was not ported to other platforms.
The players control a submarine, the Nautilus, or a destroyer, the Colossus, attempting to either destroy or rebuild an underwater city. The game the first to feature a "split screen" display to allow both players to move at the same time.